Maybe a better comparison is from some of the microframeworks for PHP. As you can see, Sinatra influenced a lot of frameworks in many languages.<p>From Slim: (<a href="http://www.slimframework.com/" rel="nofollow">http://www.slimframework.com/</a>)<p>require 'Slim/Slim.php';<p>$app = new Slim();<p>$app->get('/hello/:name', function ($name) 
{
    echo "Hello, $name!";
});<p>$app->run();<p>From Silex: (<a href="http://silex.sensiolabs.org/" rel="nofollow">http://silex.sensiolabs.org/</a>)<p>require_once __DIR__.'/silex.phar';<p>$app = new Silex\Application();<p>$app->get('/hello/{name}', function($name) use($app) { 
    return 'Hello '.$app->escape($name); 
});<p>$app->run();
